==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hercules
<hw>Her"cu*les</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Gr.
Myth.)</fld> <def>A hero, fabled to have been the son of Jupiter and
Alcmena, and celebrated for great strength, esp. for the accomplishment
of his twelve great tasks or ⟦ldquo⟧labors.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A constellation in the northern
hemisphere, near Lyra.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hercules' beetle</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any
species of <gen>Dynastes</gen>, an American genus of very large
lamellicorn beetles, esp. <spn>Dynastes hercules</spn> of South America,
which grows to a length of six inches.</cd> -- <col><b>Hercules
powder</b></col>, <cd>an explosive containing nitroglycerin; -- used for
blasting.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hercules-club</ent>⟦br⟧
